name: Lynden Douglas
text: the place is dreary and I seems like there are never any customers. The steak and cheese was good. But never never inform you of the specials. its when your seated there is a card n the table displaying the deal and you realize its too late cause you already have the food and could have gotten more had you known

name: Stephen Davis
text: Hadn't been in D'Angelo's in years. It was very good. The one pounder is great. One reason I stopped going is not enough in a sandwich. This was good...A little pricey, but good.

name: Rich Mar
text: Great service, a very pleasant group of people working there, and food is well done. I am a repeat customer.

name: Joseph Politano
text: Spent the day at the hospital, nothing to eat pulled into D'Angelo's in Weymouth best move all day

name: HEIDI NEAL
text: Always the best subs and now they have so much more. Stop by there

name: Jade Arnold-Scott
text: I've never been to D'Angelo's before, but after I had the most delicious thanksgiving turkey dinner sandwich, I can't wait to go back. The place is clean, and small. It has two different entrances, and the workers are very funny, and friendly.

name: Philip Russo
text: Place was runed down. Even though the sandwich was good was not really full. Staff was okay. Could have been cleaner.

name: Teresa Beaudoin
text: This place has been here for years.  The food is good.  Building needs a facelift.

name: Aaron Rape
text: Surprisingly good sandwich.  Had the Thanksgiving sandwich.  It's not really called that on the menu,  but that's what it is.  And it's amazing.  Get it.

name: Rob Stan
text: One in a large area chain I have visited many times clean, friendly staff, good food.
